    "The AI-based method is expected to conduct the system design according to the received pilot signal without the need for explicit channel estimation.",
    "However, this approach views the system as a black box without sufficient interpretability.The comparison between the model-driven system design and AI-driven one is presented in Table 7, which provides the basic idea, system architecture, advantages, and disadvantages of each approach.",
    "Optimization for ISACSince most tasks of ISAC networks, such as channel estimation, beamforming, and resource allocation, can be viewed as optimization problems, we compare the model-based and AI-based methods in optimization to provide a high-level viewpoint, which is presented in Table 8.The model-based methods are based on the classical optimization theory and can be proven to be optimal for some tractable problems.",
    "Nevertheless, these methods suffer from challenges in practical implementation.",
    "First, the model-based methods are tailored for the specific system models, which have a great influence on the algorithm design [66]."
